# Whitelist for debride dead-code detection.
#
# Each entry below is a method name debride flags as dead, but we know is
# actually used through a Rails convention or framework mechanism that
# debride can't see. Every entry must have a comment explaining why.
#
# NOTE: the repo currently exceeds 50 findings even with `--rails`, so the
# code_quality:debride rake task uses a RATCHET approach: it records a
# baseline count in the task itself and fails only if the count increases.
# This whitelist is for *categories* we want to permanently suppress so
# the ratchet reflects true regressions rather than Rails noise.
#
# Format: one bare method name per line. Hash/octothorpe lines are comments.
# See: https://github.com/seattlerb/debride#whitelist

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# ActiveRecord has_many / belongs_to generated reader methods.
# debride sees `has_many :foo` and flags the generated `foo` reader.
# These are exercised by associations and tests — keep them.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
podcast_memberships
users
device_codes
oauth_access_grants
oauth_access_tokens

